name: **Inishlay – _Inis Léith_**
description: Inishlay – Inis Léith L906-276 Sheet 44 A small, low, wet island, with cows, sheep, larks, mergansers, ferns, gorse, rushes, bog pools and an indented, inconvenient, rocky shore everywhere. Camp is possible but unattractive just about anywhere. Eragh Island
